SIMPLE: bezant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bezant
<hw>Be*zant"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Byzant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A gold coin of Byzantium or
Constantinople, varying in weight and value, usually (those current in
England) between a sovereign and a half sovereign. There were also white
or silver bezants.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>besant</asp>,
<asp>byzant</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A circle in <it>or</it>, i. e.,
gold, representing the gold coin called <xex>bezant</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A decoration of a flat surface, as of a band or
belt, representing circular disks lapping one upon another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bez-antler</ent>⟦br⟧
